# _headers — Cloudflare Pages custom headers
#
# Previously had a Content-Encoding: br rule for /index.wasm — that's
# gone now that build.py splits large wasm files into .part1/.part2
# instead of brotli-compressing them (see setup/build.py, section 5
# of the README). Those parts are raw bytes, not brotli, so keeping
# `Content-Encoding: br` here would make browsers try to brotli-decode
# them and fail.
#
# Left empty for now — add rules back here if/when we need custom
# caching or headers again (e.g. Cache-Control for .part1/.part2 or
# wasm-loader.js). Whatever goes here gets copied into export/ as-is
# by build.py on every run — this file (in game/template/) is the
# source of truth, don't edit the copy inside export/ directly.

# ── CSP FIX (broad/permissive on purpose) ───────────────────────────────────
# Root cause of "loads to 100%, then the page reloads itself" on some
# mobile browsers/webviews: script-src-elem and connect-src were being
# blocked (no explicit CSP was set anywhere before this, so the browser/
# host's own default kicked in and blocked things like unpkg.com and the
# wasm/pck asset fetches). This policy is intentionally wide open so
# NOTHING gets blocked while we stabilize — tighten it later once confirmed
# fixed (swap the https:/wss: wildcards for the actual backend + CDN domains).
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' https: wss: blob: data:; script-src 'self' https: blob: data: 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; script-src-elem 'self' https: blob: data: 'unsafe-inline'; worker-src 'self' https: blob: data:; connect-src 'self' https: wss: blob: data:; style-src 'self' https: 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' https: blob: data:; font-src 'self' https: data:; media-src 'self' https: blob: data:; manifest-src 'self' https:; frame-src 'self' https:; child-src 'self' https: blob:; object-src 'none'
